== Temples == * [[:en:Saidai-ji|Saidaiji (Nara)]] - A temple in [[:en:Nara Prefecture|Nara]], [[:en:Nara (city)|Nara City]]. The head temple of the [[:en:Shingon Risshu|Shingon Risshu sect]] and one of the [[:en:Nanto Shichi Daiji|Seven Great Temples of Nanto]]. * {{ill|Saidaiji (Okayama)|ja|西大寺 (岡山市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saidaiji (Okayama)|qq=}} - A temple in [[:en:Okayama Prefecture|Okayama Prefecture]], [[:en:Okayama|Okayama City]], [[:en:Higashi-ku, Okayama|Higashi-ku, Okayama]]. A special head temple of the [[:en:Kōyasan Shingon-shū|Koyasan Shingon-shu]], known for the "{{ill|Eyo (Hadaka Matsuri)|ja|会陽（裸祭）|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eyo (Hadaka Matsuri)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}." Currently, it includes [[:en:Kannon-in|Kannon-in]] and {{ill|Fumonbo Enman-in|ja|普門坊円満院|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fumonbo Enman-in|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. * {{ill|Saidaiji (Takaoka)|ja|西大寺 (高岡市)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saidaiji (Takaoka)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} - A [[:en:Jodo Shinshu Hongwanji-ha|Jodo Shinshu Honganji-ha]] temple in [[:en:Takaoka, Toyama|Takaoka City]], [[:en:Toyama Prefecture|Toyama Prefecture]]. * {{ill|Saidaiji (Higashikushira)|ja|西大寺 (東串良町)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Saidaiji (Higashikushira)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} - A [[:en:Shingon Buddhism|Shingon Buddhism]] temple in [[:en:Higashikushira, Kagoshima|Higashikushira Town]], [[:en:Kimotsuki District, Kagoshima|Kimotsuki District]], [[:en:Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima Prefecture]]. * [[:en:Sai-ji|Saiji (Kyoto)]] - A former temple in [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto City]], also known as [[:en:Sai-ji|Saiji]].
